1
00:00:55,975 --> 00:01:02,926
SEVEN YEARS IN TIBET

2
00:02:32,655 --> 00:02:36,045
Ku-Dun...

1
00:02:56,388 --> 00:02:58,146
Why must you be this way?

2
00:02:58,306 --> 00:03:01,408
Why is there always a problem?
It's a good question.

3
00:03:03,198 --> 00:03:05,020
Do you want to go home?
Do you want to turn around?

4
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:08,280
- Yes!
- It's the Himalayas!

5
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,997
How long have I been talking
about the Himalayas?

6
00:03:10,997 --> 00:03:13,171
- How long?
- Far too long.

7
00:03:14,386 --> 00:03:17,966
Horst, when we get there,
can you give me a hand, please?

8
00:03:18,063 --> 00:03:20,972
- Yes, of course.
- Ingrid, stop it.

9
00:03:38,618 --> 00:03:41,910
Let's try to make the best of this.

10
00:03:44,404 --> 00:03:46,387
Where's thls idiot
who's supposed to meet us?

11
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,392
Move!

12
00:03:53,421 --> 00:03:54,601
Mr. Harrer.

13
00:03:54,731 --> 00:03:56,328
I have your tickets.

14
00:03:56,361 --> 00:04:00,038
- I'm late. Take me to my train.
- No, you don't understand.

15
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:03,394
I am Peter Aufschnaiter.
I am leading the expedition.

16
00:04:03,394 --> 00:04:05,440
- How do you do?
- Here's our celebrity!

17
00:04:05,631 --> 00:04:07,422
Mr. Harrer?

18
00:04:07,422 --> 00:04:11,258
May I say, Mr. Harrer,
on behalf of the Reichssportsfuhrer...

19
00:04:11,289 --> 00:04:14,422
we are honored to have
such a great German hero on the team.

20
00:04:14,454 --> 00:04:16,917
Thank you, but I'm Austrian.

21
00:04:16,917 --> 00:04:19,282
Yes. but I'm sure that

22
00:04:19,282 --> 00:04:22,222
of the National Soclalist Party,
you would be proud to plant...

23
00:04:22,222 --> 00:04:26,955
our country's flag on the summit
of Nanga Parbat when you reach it.

24
00:04:27,113 --> 00:04:28,968
Hans Lobenhoffer.

25
00:04:29,095 --> 00:04:30,566
Lutz Chicken.

26
00:04:33,412 --> 00:04:35,969
And a picture with your lovely wife.

27
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:41,434
And Mr.--

28
00:04:41,498 --> 00:04:44,312
Horst lmmendorf. Family frlend.
No plcture necessary.

29
00:04:47,605 --> 00:04:49,460
When is the little one due.

30
00:04:49,619 --> 00:04:51,953
About the time my husband
reaches the base camp.

31
00:04:53,456 --> 00:04:55,725
Thank you.

32
00:04:55,757 --> 00:04:58,315
Why don't you tell the entire
stinking country our troubles?

33
00:04:59,977 --> 00:05:02,311
I'm getting on that traln.
Do you have anything you want to say?

34
00:05:06,211 --> 00:05:07,106
Fine.

35
00:05:08,386 --> 00:05:10,207
Go. Leave.

36
00:05:11,998 --> 00:05:14,428
I'll see you in four months.

37
00:05:16,281 --> 00:05:18,423
- Take good care of her, Horst.
- I will. Heinrich .

38
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:39,014
We will travel 5,000 miles.

39
00:06:39,079 --> 00:06:41,604
When we reach lndia,
we will head for the Hlmalayas...

40
00:06:41,635 --> 00:06:44,513
and the ninth highest peak
on Earth, Nanga Parbat.

41
00:06:44,641 --> 00:06:47,903
Germany calls it "Unserberg--
Our Mountain. "

42
00:06:49,085 --> 00:06:51,930
Before us, four German expeditions
attempted it.

43
00:06:51,962 --> 00:06:53,528
All failed.

44
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:57,076
Eleven climbers were killed
in storms and avalanches.

45
00:06:57,172 --> 00:07:01,584
By now, the conquest of Nanga Parbat
is a national obsession--

46
00:07:01,648 --> 00:07:03,982
a matter of German pride.

47
00:07:09,097 --> 00:07:11,430
July 29, 1939.

48
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:15,202
We have already made Camp Four
at 22.000 feet.

49
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:20,062
Overhead is the Reklak Glacier
and a difficult climb up the icefall.

50
00:07:23,099 --> 00:07:25,625
The baby must be
at least one month old now.

51
00:07:27,191 --> 00:07:30,356
I have been
so confused and dlstracted.

52
00:07:30,356 --> 00:07:33,041
I can 't climb
with my usual confldence.

53
00:07:58,584 --> 00:08:00,725
Are you all right?

54
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:07,375
Shit!

55
00:08:09,036 --> 00:08:12,618
- Are you al I right?
- Shall we come down?

56
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,516
Lost a crampon !

57
00:08:16,612 --> 00:08:18,148
Go ahead!

58
00:08:39,918 --> 00:08:42,411
The weather's getting bad.
We should rope up.

59
00:08:44,041 --> 00:08:49,253
- Did you hurt yourself back there?
- Just a scratch. I'll lead.

60
00:09:17,609 --> 00:09:19,400
Rocks!

61
00:09:19,527 --> 00:09:21,765
Look out below!

62
00:09:29,662 --> 00:09:31,962
Hold me!

63
00:09:44,015 --> 00:09:45,899
Have you got me?

64
00:09:54,595 --> 00:09:56,354
Hold me!

65
00:10:55,751 --> 00:10:58,053
You should have told me
how bad that wound was.

66
00:10:58,724 --> 00:11:01,505
I should take a look at lt.
I could sew it up.

67
00:11:06,334 --> 00:11:08,092
It's not your problem.

68
00:11:10,968 --> 00:11:12,758
Actually, it is my problem.

69
00:11:12,854 --> 00:11:15,732
- It's my life.
- What?

70
00:11:15,955 --> 00:11:19,408
When you conceal a serious injury
and put my life at risk...

71
00:11:19,504 --> 00:11:21,423
I consider th at my problem.

72
00:11:21,423 --> 00:11:24,363
No, you put your life at rlsk.
I saved it, so shut up !

73
00:11:24,394 --> 00:11:26,601
Please, it is not your place--

74
00:11:26,601 --> 00:11:28,072
Shut up !

75
00:11:29,831 --> 00:11:32,452
The next time you lle
about an lnjury, Heinrich...

76
00:11:33,410 --> 00:11:35,264
you're off the team.

77
00:11:38,461 --> 00:11:40,219
Try it.

78
00:12:57,422 --> 00:13:00,970
August 4th, Camp Five.
Some fierce storms have passed.

79
00:13:01,034 --> 00:13:03,913
My teammates are nervous
about the avalanches...

80
00:13:03,977 --> 00:13:06,310
so we 've been holed up for days.

81
00:13:06,310 --> 00:13:10,433
Aufschnalter should take advantage of
this lowland weather to make high camp.

82
00:13:10,593 --> 00:13:13,982
But he disagrees with me. Fool.

83
00:13:16,059 --> 00:13:18,874
It seems the others don 't mind
sitting here waiting...

84
00:13:19,001 --> 00:13:21,655
hoping, doing nothing.

85
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:26,256
So much time to question
one 's self is not good.

86
00:13:28,719 --> 00:13:31,531
I am beginnlng to think
this whole expedition was a mistake.

87
00:13:49,403 --> 00:13:51,258
Run ! Avalanche! Get out!

88
00:13:56,116 --> 00:13:57,300
Leave everything!

89
00:14:11,428 --> 00:14:13,316
Put that down !

90
00:14:14,626 --> 00:14:16,159
We are going down now!

91
00:14:16,287 --> 00:14:18,975
If they're frightened of a storm,
send them down to Camp Two.

92
00:14:19,038 --> 00:14:22,202
I could summit on my own !
Always give the best man his shot!

93
00:14:22,331 --> 00:14:24,728
He's trying to tell us
he's the best man.

94
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:26,902
Give me two Sherpas.
I can make Camp Six by tonight...

95
00:14:27,062 --> 00:14:28,820
and my final attack tomorrow!

96
00:14:28,948 --> 00:14:31,727
- We are going down now as a team!
- I've earned that peak!

97
00:14:31,825 --> 00:14:33,615
- I want th at peak!
- As a team! That's an order!

98
00:14:33,744 --> 00:14:37,132
That is an order! An order!

99
00:14:38,283 --> 00:14:39,753
Follow me!

100
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:42,538
Dalai Lama photo. Good protection.

101
00:15:42,602 --> 00:15:45,415
Take it. Si Hib.

102
00:15:45,415 --> 00:15:48,612
No, that means nothing to me.

103
00:15:48,709 --> 00:15:51,266
Dalai Lama. Dalai Lama photo.

104
00:15:51,331 --> 00:15:52,992
Si Hib, take it.

105
00:15:53,089 --> 00:15:54,879
Good protection for you.

106
00:16:08,049 --> 00:16:10,606
Good afternoon, Herr Harrer.

107
00:16:10,637 --> 00:16:12,717
Well, let's hope that Germany
retreats from Poland...

108
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:14,858
as quickly as you did
from your mountain.

109
00:16:14,955 --> 00:16:17,319
It might save you some prison time.

110
00:16:18,951 --> 00:16:20,933
What is this? Who are you?

111
00:16:20,965 --> 00:16:25,761
- I'm sorry, but you're under arrest.
- What charge? Failure to summit?

112
00:16:25,824 --> 00:16:27,294
I'm afraid not.

113
00:16:28,413 --> 00:16:32,313
You see, war has been declared between
Hls Majesty's Government and Germany.

114
00:16:32,439 --> 00:16:37,269
So all enemy aliens on British Empire
soil are now prisoners of war.

115
00:17:19,243 --> 00:17:22,088
- Stop, or I'll shoot!
- Hands up!

116
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:24,708
No, you don't understand!
I'm Austrian ! I'm a cllmber!

117
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:27,873
I have nothing to do
with your silly war!

118
00:17:33,086 --> 00:17:36,601
I can walk myself.
This is an insult!

119
00:17:38,391 --> 00:17:41,333
You think you have the last word,
but you don't!

120
00:17:41,429 --> 00:17:43,986
Pigs! All of you, pigs!

121
00:17:56,965 --> 00:17:58,787
October 15, 1939.

122
00:18:01,343 --> 00:18:04,255
Reaching prison camp,
I make a promise to myself.

123
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:10,103
I will be lying beside lngrid before
the summer solstice of the new year.

124
00:18:11,957 --> 00:18:14,291
The Hlmalayas are right in front of us.

125
00:18:14,418 --> 00:18:17,168
It will be easy to escape
and get lost in them.

126
00:18:29,508 --> 00:18:32,993
My fourth escape attempt
brings me no closer to my goal.

127
00:18:33,985 --> 00:18:36,318
How far did you get this time?

128
00:18:36,382 --> 00:18:40,186
All I have achieved is a certaln
dubious celebrity among the prisoners.

129
00:19:03,971 --> 00:19:07,647
If only my hand could express
what is ln my heart.

130
00:19:21,584 --> 00:19:23,757
I hear the guards
are mailing letters for you.

131
00:19:24,972 --> 00:19:26,092
Yes.

132
00:19:26,156 --> 00:19:28,394
Would you mail these?

133
00:19:30,951 --> 00:19:33,254
Thank you.

134
00:19:33,254 --> 00:19:35,587
Hey, Heinrich, have you read this book?

135
00:19:35,651 --> 00:19:37,919
It was checked out to you.

136
00:19:42,970 --> 00:19:45,751
- We need to talk to you.
- What about?

137
00:19:45,846 --> 00:19:47,286
About this.

138
00:19:55,375 --> 00:19:58,219
Impressive. When do you plan to leave?

139
00:19:58,219 --> 00:20:00,202
After monsoon season. And you?

140
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:05,830
I see you've chosen
my route through Tibet.

141
00:20:05,989 --> 00:20:09,729
The few foreigners who have tried
never came back. So, good luck.

142
00:20:09,794 --> 00:20:12,925
- Would you like to come with us?
- Why?

143
00:20:12,990 --> 00:20:16,058
After all, you are the authority
on jailbreak around here.

144
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:19,607
- We could benefit from your experience.
- Please.

145
00:20:21,110 --> 00:20:23,282
Stop this embarrassing charade.

146
00:20:24,625 --> 00:20:28,335
Every time you escape,
the patrols are doubled and tripled.

147
00:20:28,399 --> 00:20:31,531
It is making life very difficult
for the rest of us.

148
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:34,601
I prefer to travel on my own,
but thanks for thinking of me.

149
00:20:42,944 --> 00:20:44,734
The mailman has come.

150
00:21:21,978 --> 00:21:23,415
Dear Heinrlch:

151
00:21:23,608 --> 00:21:27,189
Please sign the enclosed dlvorce papers
and send them to my lawyer.

152
00:21:27,189 --> 00:21:31,056
Horst and I intend to be married
as soon as the divorce is flnalized.

153
00:21:31,088 --> 00:21:32,973
As for your letter, yes.

154
00:21:33,039 --> 00:21:36,842
Your son, Rolf Harrer, was born
while you were climbing the mountain.

155
00:21:36,939 --> 00:21:40,710
He is now two years old
and calls Horst "papa. "

156
00:21:40,774 --> 00:21:42,852
When he is old enough,
I will tell him...

157
00:21:42,916 --> 00:21:45,441
his real father was lost
in the Himalayas.

158
00:21:45,505 --> 00:21:47,519
It seems the kindest thing
to say consldering...

159
00:21:47,519 --> 00:21:49,950
you never wanted the child anyway.

160
00:21:50,014 --> 00:21:52,442
Needless to say,
I have no intention...

161
00:21:52,603 --> 00:21:56,117
of "resolving our differences "
as you suggested.

162
00:21:56,182 --> 00:21:59,508
They were resolved
the moment you left Austria.

163
00:21:59,571 --> 00:22:02,640
I'm sorry you have been
imprisoned ln lndia...

164
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:06,733
and hope this dreadful war will soon
be over for everyone's sake.

165
00:22:06,764 --> 00:22:08,298
Ingrid.

166
00:23:32,854 --> 00:23:34,101
I'm coming with you.

167
00:23:42,605 --> 00:23:43,916
This is your plan?

168
00:23:47,719 --> 00:23:50,759
In my humble opinion,
this is ridiculous.

169
00:23:50,854 --> 00:23:53,634
Then since you are so humble,
we won't ask your opinion.

170
00:24:37,431 --> 00:24:39,507
Open the charts. Turn around.

171
00:24:39,572 --> 00:24:43,376
Keep your back to the gate.
Open the charts!

172
00:24:57,986 --> 00:25:01,055
Keep talking. Wait for my signal.

173
00:25:02,205 --> 00:25:04,125
We are clear. Okay.

174
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:18,542
Open the gates!

175
00:25:25,831 --> 00:25:29,252
See to this. Open the gates!

176
00:26:03,072 --> 00:26:04,992
I'm going off on my own.

177
00:26:05,056 --> 00:26:06,974
So, good luck.

178
00:26:41,115 --> 00:26:46,773
First escape from prlson camp,
November 18, 1939.

179
00:26:46,869 --> 00:26:49,844
Rolf Harrer--
three and a half months old.

180
00:26:51,984 --> 00:26:55,917
My 30th birthday, July 6, 1941.

181
00:26:55,982 --> 00:27:00,615
Rolf Harrer-- exactly one year,
11 months and 26 days.

182
00:27:02,917 --> 00:27:06,211
Last escape from Dehra Dun.
Rolf Harrer--

183
00:29:28,373 --> 00:29:32,464
Take two and sleep it off.
I'll send you a bill in the morning.

184
00:29:36,398 --> 00:29:38,156
What are you doing here?

185
00:29:38,315 --> 00:29:43,269
I missed you so much.
I thought I'd pay you a visit.

186
00:29:46,978 --> 00:29:49,408
What about the others?

187
00:29:49,441 --> 00:29:51,997
The ltalians were caught
outside Nelang.

188
00:29:52,061 --> 00:29:55,002
Lutz and Hans got sick
and had to turn back.

189
00:29:56,985 --> 00:29:59,765
- Sorry to hear that.
- I'm sure you're heartbroken.

190
00:30:02,292 --> 00:30:06,160
May I impose upon your generous nature
and camp here tonight?

191
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:08,078
Be my guest.

192
00:30:08,205 --> 00:30:11,243
Thank you.
It is very gracious of you.

193
00:30:30,871 --> 00:30:32,692
- Good.
- What else do you have in there?

194
00:30:32,790 --> 00:30:34,931
A ten-piece orchestra?

195
00:30:35,027 --> 00:30:39,214
By the way, I heard
the Japanese have retreated...

196
00:30:39,245 --> 00:30:43,082
all the way back to Shanghai so even
if you make it to the Chinese border...

197
00:30:43,082 --> 00:30:45,127
you may have dlfficulty
catchlng up with them.

198
00:30:45,127 --> 00:30:47,653
I don 't care if they're repelled
all the way back to Tokyo.

199
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:49,733
You should if you want
to get back to Austria.

200
00:30:50,659 --> 00:30:52,609
- But I don't.
- Don't what?

201
00:30:54,943 --> 00:30:57,435
- Plan to go back.
- Why not?

202
00:31:00,632 --> 00:31:03,381
No particular reason.

203
00:31:03,509 --> 00:31:05,268
When you get there, tell my wife...

204
00:31:05,268 --> 00:31:09,200
that two years in prison camp is roughly
equivalent to four years of marriage.

205
00:31:09,296 --> 00:31:11,663
And I'm glad to be free of them both.

206
00:31:14,539 --> 00:31:18,631
I'm not golng back either,
not until this shameful war is over.

207
00:31:18,759 --> 00:31:21,319
- And where are you headed?
- Tibet.

208
00:31:21,382 --> 00:31:25,792
Then on to China.

209
00:31:26,943 --> 00:31:28,190
And you ?

210
00:31:28,254 --> 00:31:32,664
By my calculations, the Chinese border
is 2,058 kilometers away.

211
00:31:32,664 --> 00:31:35,096
Tibet is 68.

212
00:31:35,191 --> 00:31:39,091
It's a long way to travel
with such a heavy load.

213
00:31:40,308 --> 00:31:42,544
No, just full of food.

214
00:31:42,608 --> 00:31:45,293
- Precisely.
- Mine.

215
00:31:46,923 --> 00:31:48,458
That's too bad.

216
00:31:48,521 --> 00:31:52,197
Those mountains are treacherous.
There are glaciers to be crossed.

217
00:31:52,326 --> 00:31:54,403
If you had roped up to me,
I could have kept you alive.

218
00:31:54,434 --> 00:31:56,769
Considering your performance
the last time we roped up...

219
00:31:56,769 --> 00:31:58,880
I think I'm safer without you.

220
00:32:02,972 --> 00:32:04,187
Of course.

221
00:32:08,373 --> 00:32:12,626
But I think you are wrong about
that Tibetan border calculatlon.

222
00:32:12,626 --> 00:32:15,662
By my measurements,
it is 65 kilometers.

223
00:32:18,730 --> 00:32:20,619
Care to wager a kilo of food on that?

224
00:32:23,398 --> 00:32:27,204
All you've got is some stale crackers.

225
00:32:28,610 --> 00:32:31,198
But I'm right. I'll win.

226
00:33:11,064 --> 00:33:13,780
Tibet, the roof of the world.

227
00:33:13,908 --> 00:33:16,848
It feels as though we have
ascended a medieval stone fortress...

228
00:33:16,977 --> 00:33:19,600
towering above the center of Asla.

229
00:33:19,727 --> 00:33:22,125
This ls the highest country on Earth.

230
00:33:22,125 --> 00:33:24,009
And the most isolated.

231
00:33:32,674 --> 00:33:34,177
There it is.

232
00:33:35,104 --> 00:33:36,958
Tibet.

233
00:33:38,044 --> 00:33:41,592
- Exactly 68 kilometers.
- Congratulations.

234
00:33:42,904 --> 00:33:45,109
Unfortunately, you've eaten
all your winnings.

235
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:03,683
Yes.

236
00:34:03,747 --> 00:34:06,625
Just smile and say yes.
It's better that way.

237
00:34:10,046 --> 00:34:12,091
It's amazing what you learn
in prison, isn't it?

238
00:34:21,618 --> 00:34:23,119
Tibet.

239
00:34:25,773 --> 00:34:28,203
- No foreigners allowed in Tlbet.
- Oh, please!

240
00:34:28,299 --> 00:34:29,640
No foreigner!

241
00:34:29,768 --> 00:34:31,718
Oh, please!

242
00:34:38,592 --> 00:34:41,661
Yes. Thank you. Of course.

243
00:35:08,099 --> 00:35:09,955
No translation needed.

244
00:35:40,228 --> 00:35:42,433
Some people are glad to see us.

245
00:35:42,593 --> 00:35:44,638
Don't let it get to your head.

246
00:35:44,767 --> 00:35:48,794
When the Tibetans clap hands, it means
they are driving out evil forces.

247
00:35:54,612 --> 00:35:56,467
We need to find food.

248
00:36:10,309 --> 00:36:13,794
It is the prophecy. It says here...

249
00:36:13,794 --> 00:36:17,854
in the final testament
of great thirteenth Dalai Lama.

250
00:36:17,982 --> 00:36:21,594
"It may happen that, in Tibet,
religions and government...

251
00:36:21,594 --> 00:36:24,311
will be attacked by outside forces.

252
00:36:24,409 --> 00:36:27,541
Unless we can guard our own country...

253
00:36:27,604 --> 00:36:30,610
monks and their monasteries
will be destroyed.

254
00:36:30,768 --> 00:36:34,285
The lands and property
of government officials will be seized.

255
00:36:34,413 --> 00:36:38,091
The Dalai Lama an d all
the revered holders of the faith...

256
00:36:38,154 --> 00:36:40,519
will disappear and become nameless."

257
00:36:40,551 --> 00:36:44,194
Now you understand why we are not
welcome to forelgners here?

258
00:36:44,259 --> 00:36:48,192
Yes, but you must understand
we're not here to threaten or harm.

259
00:36:48,256 --> 00:36:50,463
We just need food,
and then we'll be on our--

260
00:36:50,463 --> 00:36:52,475
His Excellency, the Garpon.

261
00:36:58,614 --> 00:37:02,066
Your Eminence, we're happy to see you.

262
00:37:02,226 --> 00:37:04,944
We wanted to apologize.

263
00:37:04,975 --> 00:37:06,541
Apologize.

264
00:37:09,417 --> 00:37:12,295
And give you this really special gift.

265
00:37:14,788 --> 00:37:16,802
Please, from us.

266
00:37:16,962 --> 00:37:20,065
Long live the Dalai Lama,
Hi s Holiness.

267
00:37:26,649 --> 00:37:29,526
Thank you for the picture.
Go back to lndla!

268
00:37:35,762 --> 00:37:39,917
Two days into Tibet 's western frontier
and we are graciously klcked out.

269
00:37:41,036 --> 00:37:43,114
Our guides have strict orders
to escort us...

270
00:37:43,273 --> 00:37:46,213
to the lndian border
some 40 kllometers away...

271
00:37:46,340 --> 00:37:49,091
and to shoot us
if we attempt escape.

272
00:38:21,442 --> 00:38:23,455
Must mean hello.

273
00:38:23,519 --> 00:38:25,726
As long as they don't try to kiss me.

274
00:38:29,754 --> 00:38:32,184
We have to stock up. I'm broke.

275
00:38:33,621 --> 00:38:35,413
Don't look at me.

276
00:38:35,540 --> 00:38:38,769
We have to eat. Peter.

277
00:38:40,048 --> 00:38:42,287
It is not negotiable.

278
00:38:42,287 --> 00:38:44,811
My father gave it to me
when I climbed Mount BI anc.

279
00:38:44,875 --> 00:38:46,857
Everyone's climbed Mount Blanc.

280
00:38:46,952 --> 00:38:49,063
If I had a watch like this,
I would trade it.

281
00:39:30,973 --> 00:39:33,339
- Where did you get this jacket?
- North Tibet.

282
00:39:33,434 --> 00:39:35,769
Communlsm soldier come from Chin a.
Very nice.

283
00:39:35,834 --> 00:39:38,741
They give food, money. Very nice.
Communism soldier.

284
00:39:41,298 --> 00:39:43,536
You like military uniforms, yes?

285
00:39:44,624 --> 00:39:48,331
I have German army boots.
For you. Yes?

286
00:39:48,395 --> 00:39:49,643
Wait.

287
00:39:57,988 --> 00:40:00,415
Give me these, for the guards.

288
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:01,984
Look!

289
00:40:07,865 --> 00:40:09,849
Like this. You like?

290
00:40:11,990 --> 00:40:13,843
Very good. They're tough.

291
00:40:13,971 --> 00:40:17,519
My friend, shall I show you
how German soldiers march?

292
00:40:22,539 --> 00:40:24,650
You must make this face.

293
00:40:33,503 --> 00:40:35,838
Come! Yes.

294
00:40:35,870 --> 00:40:37,435
Stop!

295
00:40:39,256 --> 00:40:42,263
Excellent. Yes.
You, with practice.

296
00:40:43,062 --> 00:40:46,610
Now, I will show you
how German soldiers run.

297
00:40:50,863 --> 00:40:52,717
Stand like this.

298
00:41:39,039 --> 00:41:40,957
Guess what?

299
00:41:42,556 --> 00:41:44,313
All clear.

300
00:42:06,276 --> 00:42:08,768
Know what time it is?

301
00:42:11,166 --> 00:42:15,417
You think I'm so happy
to be traveling with you...

302
00:42:15,449 --> 00:42:17,847
I should foot the bill?

303
00:42:17,943 --> 00:42:21,299
You are such a blg man
you don't need to contribute?

304
00:42:22,323 --> 00:42:23,761
You have a problem?

305
00:42:23,922 --> 00:42:25,327
Remind me...

306
00:42:26,416 --> 00:42:29,420
what you said at the bazaar back there.

307
00:42:29,452 --> 00:42:34,599
"If I had a watch like that,
I would trade it."

308
00:42:36,804 --> 00:42:39,524
You do not have one.

309
00:42:39,588 --> 00:42:42,784
You cheap, lying bastard!
You have three!

310
00:42:54,325 --> 00:42:56,723
This is junk
from some ltalian prisoners.

311
00:42:56,723 --> 00:42:59,055
I don't give a shit!

312
00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:01,196
Haven't you ever heard of a principle?

313
00:43:01,196 --> 00:43:03,594
What principle?

314
00:43:03,722 --> 00:43:06,599
You want a watch?
Go ahead. Pick one.

315
00:43:06,662 --> 00:43:08,996
- And keep your principles.
- Look at you !

316
00:43:10,595 --> 00:43:13,439
Caught being a selfish brat
and you're gloating !

317
00:43:13,600 --> 00:43:16,381
You're acting like an old woman.
What do you want?

318
00:43:16,381 --> 00:43:19,673
Try apologizing.

319
00:43:19,673 --> 00:43:21,656
Try feeling a little remorse.

320
00:43:21,784 --> 00:43:25,140
And if all else fail s,
try wiping that smirk off your face!

321
00:43:25,140 --> 00:43:27,569
Take your stinking watch
and shut up!

322
00:43:28,784 --> 00:43:32,716
I don't need another boring sermon from
some frustrated glorified tour guide.

323
00:43:42,052 --> 00:43:44,417
No wonder you are always alone.

324
00:43:44,449 --> 00:43:47,518
No one can stand
your miserable company.

325
00:44:18,208 --> 00:44:20,478
Please, take them.

326
00:44:29,141 --> 00:44:31,410
It was wrong of me to hide them.

327
00:44:42,184 --> 00:44:44,420
- Keep this.
- No.

328
00:44:48,928 --> 00:44:53,181
I didn't deserve It either.
Go ahead.

329
00:45:09,327 --> 00:45:12,203
He'll be three and a half years old now.

330
00:45:16,391 --> 00:45:19,682
Pretty soon, she'll tell him
I was lost in the Himalayas.

331
00:45:22,943 --> 00:45:24,255
Which is fine.

332
00:45:26,109 --> 00:45:27,675
Why?

333
00:45:30,648 --> 00:45:33,654
Better a dead father
than a lousy father.

334
00:45:35,412 --> 00:45:37,297
Write him a letter.

335
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:40,718
Let him know you're still alive.

336
00:45:49,286 --> 00:45:51,395
New York.

337
00:45:55,838 --> 00:45:57,276
Venice.

338
00:46:02,776 --> 00:46:05,811
- Paris.
- Your Holiness, where are you?

339
00:46:05,973 --> 00:46:07,922
It ls time for your lesson.

340
00:46:13,039 --> 00:46:17,769
Your Holiness, where are you?
It is time for your lesson.

341
00:46:20,871 --> 00:46:22,277
Dear Rolf Harrer:

342
00:46:23,332 --> 00:46:25,443
I'm a person you don 't know...

343
00:46:25,602 --> 00:46:28,319
a man you 've never met.

344
00:46:28,319 --> 00:46:30,939
But you are someone
who occupies my mind...

345
00:46:31,035 --> 00:46:32,794
and my heart...

346
00:46:32,858 --> 00:46:34,904
in this dlstant land
where I have gone.

347
00:46:36,981 --> 00:46:40,819
If you can imagine a hidden place
tucked safely away from the world...

348
00:46:40,851 --> 00:46:44,078
concealed by walls
of high, snowcapped mountains--

349
00:46:44,206 --> 00:46:47,564
a place rich with all the strange
beauty of your nighttime dreams--

350
00:46:49,194 --> 00:46:50,983
then you know where I am.

351
00:46:53,925 --> 00:46:55,779
In the country
where I am traveling, Tibet...

352
00:46:56,643 --> 00:46:59,839
people believe if they walk
long distances to holy places...

353
00:46:59,998 --> 00:47:02,652
It purifles the bad deeds
they've committed.

354
00:47:02,716 --> 00:47:05,146
They believe
the more difficult the journey...

355
00:47:05,210 --> 00:47:07,767
the greater the depth
of purification.

356
00:47:10,931 --> 00:47:14,608
I've been walking from one faraway
place to the next for many years--

357
00:47:15,759 --> 00:47:17,805
as long as you have lived.

358
00:47:18,956 --> 00:47:22,313
I have seen seasons change
across the high plateaus.

359
00:47:22,313 --> 00:47:25,542
I have seen wild kiangs
migrate south in winter...

360
00:47:25,638 --> 00:47:28,386
and sweep back across the fields
when spring appears.

361
00:47:30,305 --> 00:47:32,670
In this place,
where time stands still...

362
00:47:32,798 --> 00:47:34,621
it seems that everything is moving...

363
00:47:35,517 --> 00:47:37,339
including me.

364
00:47:40,632 --> 00:47:42,453
I can 't say I know where I'm going...

365
00:47:42,550 --> 00:47:45,425
nor whether my bad deeds
can be purified.

366
00:47:46,864 --> 00:47:49,837
There are so many things
I have done which I regret.

367
00:47:51,021 --> 00:47:54,602
But when I come to a full stop,
I hope you will understand...

368
00:47:54,634 --> 00:47:58,117
that the distance between us
is not as great as it seems.

369
00:47:59,746 --> 00:48:01,443
Wlth deep affection...

370
00:48:01,507 --> 00:48:04,958
your father, Heinrlch Harrer.

371
00:48:05,789 --> 00:48:07,292
Get up.

372
00:48:16,946 --> 00:48:18,481
My God!

373
00:48:22,924 --> 00:48:24,746
I'll give you these.

374
00:48:44,375 --> 00:48:46,645
Yellow head!

375
00:48:46,773 --> 00:48:49,522
- No! Wait! We have nothing!
- Give me money!

376
00:48:49,650 --> 00:48:50,961
We have no money!

377
00:48:50,961 --> 00:48:52,880
Give me watch !

378
00:48:52,944 --> 00:48:55,436
- Give me clothes!
- We have nothing for you !

379
00:49:58,125 --> 00:49:59,948
Wait!

380
00:50:05,414 --> 00:50:07,301
Where are you headed?

381
00:50:11,682 --> 00:50:14,302
I have permit.

382
00:50:25,331 --> 00:50:27,122
Lhasa. I have permit.

383
00:51:11,653 --> 00:51:15,680
It is unseemly for the spiritual leader
of Tibet to spy on people.

384
00:51:20,412 --> 00:51:24,249
Only a month ago, we were certain
of death at the hands of bandits.

385
00:51:24,345 --> 00:51:29,842
And today, we have reached the gates
of the forbidden city of Lhasa.

386
00:51:29,969 --> 00:51:32,623
It is as difficult a goal as Mecca...

387
00:51:32,688 --> 00:51:37,292
and preclsely as attractive
because it ls closed to all foreigners.

388
00:51:38,636 --> 00:51:40,968
Even in our miserable condition...

389
00:51:40,968 --> 00:51:43,845
we feel the lure
of Tlbet 's holiest city...

390
00:51:43,972 --> 00:51:46,212
home of the Dalai Lama.

391
00:51:47,074 --> 00:51:49,822
Only a few foreigners
had penetrated its mysteries.

392
00:52:52,256 --> 00:52:55,294
Oh, my God!

393
00:53:06,610 --> 00:53:09,423
- Is It over?
- No. it is not over.

394
00:53:49,128 --> 00:53:52,005
You are invited to stay
for lunch, if you like.

395
00:53:53,126 --> 00:53:54,629
We'd like that very much.

396
00:53:56,322 --> 00:53:58,943
I am Tsarong. Welcome to my home.

397
00:53:58,974 --> 00:54:01,308
I am Peter.

398
00:54:05,526 --> 00:54:07,671
Lord Chamberlain, may I request...

399
00:54:07,734 --> 00:54:11,186
an audlence with the regent
and ministers of the cabinet?

400
00:54:11,282 --> 00:54:15,536
It's about two foreigners
who came to Lhasa.

401
00:54:20,328 --> 00:54:22,278
With respect, Rinpoche...

402
00:54:23,207 --> 00:54:26,115
If your intention is to stop the Chinese
from recruiting political allies...

403
00:54:26,243 --> 00:54:31,390
then demanding that they stop
trying to bribe monks...

404
00:54:31,422 --> 00:54:33,788
is not the most effective tactic.

405
00:54:35,994 --> 00:54:40,052
I asked the opinion of the ministers,
not that of a mere secretary.

406
00:54:43,282 --> 00:54:46,638
Of course. Forgive me.

407
00:54:46,638 --> 00:54:48,460
You may leave now.

408
00:54:48,557 --> 00:54:51,945
Start translating the letter
as written .

409
00:54:51,945 --> 00:54:54,471
Of course.

410
00:55:11,032 --> 00:55:14,227
Do you realize how many men
could survive such an ordeal?

411
00:55:15,122 --> 00:55:17,009
We should respect them.

412
00:55:17,104 --> 00:55:21,005
If we return them to lndla,
they'll surely go back to prison.

413
00:55:21,068 --> 00:55:24,202
But they have no purpose here,
Kungo Tsarong. No place to live.

414
00:55:24,330 --> 00:55:27,974
I have invited them to stay
at my guest quarters...

415
00:55:28,070 --> 00:55:32,193
assuming you would grant them permission
to remain in Lhasa, of course.

416
00:55:32,322 --> 00:55:35,038
Invited them to stay at your place?

417
00:55:35,613 --> 00:55:36,988
But why?

418
00:55:37,116 --> 00:55:39,930
Must one have reason
to help those in need?

419
00:55:42,934 --> 00:55:44,469
Beast.

420
00:55:49,137 --> 00:55:50,959
I think she said you stink.

421
00:56:24,622 --> 00:56:27,339
You do not need
to introduce yourselves.

422
00:56:27,403 --> 00:56:29,289
I know who you are.

423
00:56:30,087 --> 00:56:32,326
I am Pema Lhaki.

424
00:56:32,390 --> 00:56:36,001
Ngawang wishes to make a gift to you,
so please take your clothes off.

425
00:56:40,031 --> 00:56:42,109
Let's get started.
I don't have all day.

426
00:56:42,173 --> 00:56:47,256
Well, this is most kind
of Ngawang Jigme.

427
00:56:47,287 --> 00:56:49,747
Who is he to be so thoughtful?

428
00:56:49,811 --> 00:56:52,082
Secretary to the ministers
of the government.

429
00:56:52,210 --> 00:56:54,736
He wished to make you
a gift of new clothes.

430
00:56:54,799 --> 00:56:57,740
Please select your preferred
article of clothing.

431
00:57:00,299 --> 00:57:01,864
You're a seamstress?

432
00:57:01,864 --> 00:57:05,764
I am a tailor, sir,
the only tailor in Lhasa...

433
00:57:05,860 --> 00:57:09,600
who has been to Calcutta and
can reproduce these silly costumes.

434
00:57:12,062 --> 00:57:14,939
So, I pick?

435
00:57:15,066 --> 00:57:17,368
Yes, choose whichever you like.

436
00:57:21,045 --> 00:57:23,125
- And you can make any of these?
- Yes.

437
00:57:24,019 --> 00:57:26,800
- Very good.
- Did you make this?

438
00:57:26,864 --> 00:57:29,996
- Yes.
- Beautiful.

439
00:57:29,996 --> 00:57:31,659
- Th ank you.
- Do you like this?

440
00:57:31,787 --> 00:57:33,609
Whichever you like.

441
00:57:36,614 --> 00:57:39,108
I will have this handsome tweed jacket.

442
00:57:39,204 --> 00:57:42,720
And this pair of sporting
woolen trousers, please.

443
00:57:42,752 --> 00:57:45,117
- Good choice.
- Thanks.

444
00:57:45,150 --> 00:57:47,035
And you, sir?

445
00:57:50,455 --> 00:57:53,015
- Perhaps you could choose for me.
- Thank you.

446
00:57:57,010 --> 00:58:00,336
Please, sir, take off your chu-pa.
I would like to measure.

447
00:58:12,642 --> 00:58:14,336
Stand still, please.

448
00:58:18,429 --> 00:58:20,218
Thls way, please.

449
00:58:24,630 --> 00:58:26,452
- Stand still.
- Sorry.

450
00:58:35,018 --> 00:58:37,643
- No moving, please.
- I'm sorry.

451
00:58:46,880 --> 00:58:49,055
That way, you will never fall.
It's perfect.

452
00:58:49,118 --> 00:58:52,636
Still, walking up mountain s
is a fool's pleasure, Heinrich.

453
00:58:52,731 --> 00:58:54,937
Not so foolish, really.

454
00:58:59,444 --> 00:59:00,786
Look at this.

455
00:59:03,152 --> 00:59:04,621
Go ahead.

456
00:59:09,195 --> 00:59:12,295
That's after I climbed
the Eiger North Face.

457
00:59:16,642 --> 00:59:21,789
That's Olympics.
Gold medal. Not important.

458
00:59:21,853 --> 00:59:26,616
Then this is another great difference
between our civilization and yours.

459
00:59:26,649 --> 00:59:28,375
You admire the man...

460
00:59:28,375 --> 00:59:32,403
who pushes his way to the top
in any walk of life...

461
00:59:32,466 --> 00:59:35,759
while we admire the man
who abandons his ego.

462
00:59:38,413 --> 00:59:41,610
The average Tibetan wouldn't think
to thrust himself forward this way.

463
00:59:57,785 --> 00:59:59,736
Gentlemen.

464
01:00:02,964 --> 01:00:05,330
- I'm sorry. Have we met?
- No, we have not.

465
01:00:05,361 --> 01:00:07,953
I am Ngawang Jigme.

466
01:00:11,948 --> 01:00:14,728
- Yes, of course.
- Forgive us.

467
01:00:14,792 --> 01:00:17,445
Thank you for your generous gift.

468
01:00:17,605 --> 01:00:19,619
It's wonderful. Thank you.

469
01:00:21,762 --> 01:00:26,111
You are most welcome.
I am sure we will meet again.

470
01:00:36,978 --> 01:00:40,688
Perhaps you could help us explain...

471
01:00:40,751 --> 01:00:42,763
why the min isters...

472
01:00:42,763 --> 01:00:46,474
demand that the Chinese government...

473
01:00:46,538 --> 01:00:50,276
"...cease making generous
financlal contributions...

474
01:00:50,437 --> 01:00:54,338
to Tibetan monasteries."

475
01:00:54,402 --> 01:00:58,556
Do our gifts displease your government?

476
01:00:58,620 --> 01:01:02,648
I cannot speak for the regent
nor the ministers, Excellence.

477
01:01:02,746 --> 01:01:04,950
I am only a mere secretary.

478
01:01:05,014 --> 01:01:09,331
Not for long, I presume.
Sit down.

479
01:01:16,811 --> 01:01:20,071
A man of such obvious talent
cannot be satisfied...

480
01:01:20,104 --> 01:01:24,324
with just translating letters.

481
01:01:24,388 --> 01:01:27,297
Your diplomatic skill...

482
01:01:27,456 --> 01:01:30,111
would be richly rewarded here.

483
01:01:33,178 --> 01:01:36,792
Serving my country faithfully
is reward enough, Excellence.

484
01:01:39,925 --> 01:01:41,778
I ask permission to take my leave.

485
01:02:49,549 --> 01:02:52,077
It looks like we're both in need
of a good tailor today.

486
01:02:52,971 --> 01:02:54,474
Yes, there's a--

487
01:02:55,434 --> 01:02:57,671
Please, take a seat.

488
01:03:39,613 --> 01:03:41,979
Do you like these?
I'll buy them for you.

489
01:03:42,105 --> 01:03:45,144
Thank you,
but I don't eat much meat.

490
01:03:45,209 --> 01:03:48,213
- Don't eat meat?
- He says they are knives from West.

491
01:03:48,308 --> 01:03:50,545
You put them on your feet to cut meat.

492
01:03:54,415 --> 01:03:56,335
They are ice skates.

493
01:03:56,397 --> 01:03:58,889
You put them on your feet...

494
01:03:58,889 --> 01:04:00,105
to skate...

495
01:04:00,201 --> 01:04:02,758
to glide--
